, being creative, and getting work done. This is especially clear in the phone’s camera system.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThe camera features of the Galaxy S25 Edge are a supposed to be a big improvement in mobile photography. With a 200-megapixel wide lens, the phone provides professional-quality photos, letting users take extremely sharp and colorful pictures. Additionally, the AI turns the camera into a smart lens, automatically recognizing subjects and scenes to adjust settings for the best possible shots. The AI also helps with editing and sharing images, making improving and distributing photos after they’re taken easier.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eSamsung claims the S25 Edge brings major upgrades across many areas of smartphone functionality. The company did not share how it will be an upgrade, but it is clear that Samsung thinks the S25 Edge will raise the bar for smartphone performance and design.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eTo encourage early purchases, Samsung is offering a $50 Samsung credit to customers who pre-order the phone. It\u0026#39;s honestly not much, especially considering that newer flagship phones tend to cost over $1,000, so you really shouldn\u0026#39;t take this credit into account when pre-ordering. It\u0026#39;s not clear yet how much the Galaxy S25 Edge will cost.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026#39;re interested, make sure to go to the official Samsung pages, preferably \u003ca href=\"https://www.youtube.com/samsung\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eYouTube\u003c/a\u003e, on May 12 at 8pm ET. This will be when we find out what is happening with the new Samsung Galaxy S25 Edge.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eSource: Samsung\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cul\u003e\n                                    \u003cli\u003e\n                    \u003ca href=\"https://www.howtogeek.com/category/android/\" title=\"Android\"\u003e\n                                              